I'm Bob Callahan.

04:36.832 --> 04:38.366
<i>So, where are you headed?</i>

04:38.368 --> 04:39.666
<i>Home.</i>

04:39.668 --> 04:41.135
I've been on the road
for a while.

04:41.137 --> 04:42.036
Doing what?

04:42.038 --> 04:44.404
Oh, this and that.
I'm in sales.

04:44.406 --> 04:45.671
Oh. Selling what?

04:45.673 --> 04:46.907
<i>As I said,
a little of this...</i>

04:46.909 --> 04:48.377
<i>...little of that.</i>

04:49.878 --> 04:51.111
What are you looking for?

04:58.021 --> 05:00.186
- So, you like horses?
- What?

05:00.188 --> 05:03.590
- That thing you're...
- Oh! Yes! Yeah, I do.

05:03.592 --> 05:06.327
So, you're a cowgirl
who likes stealing cars?

05:06.329 --> 05:08.861
- What else am I missing?
- That's pretty much it.

05:08.863 --> 05:10.863
I have three horses.
I live in the country.

05:10.865 --> 05:12.500
- Three horses?
- I love to ride.

05:12.502 --> 05:13.633
- Yeah.
- What are their names?

05:13.635 --> 05:15.501
- The horses?
- Yeah.

05:15.503 --> 05:17.537
Wiley, Clementine,
and Dorothy Jean.

05:17.539 --> 05:19.138
Dorothy Jean?

05:19.140 --> 05:21.442
Sounds like my kinda gal.
Dorothy Jean.

05:21.444 --> 05:22.743
Do you ride?

05:22.745 --> 05:24.911
Me? No.
No, never. Never have.

05:24.913 --> 05:27.582
- But it's on my list.
- What list is that?

05:27.584 --> 05:29.450
Things I want to do
but haven't done yet.

05:29.452 --> 05:30.954
Well, you better hurry up.

05:32.055 --> 05:33.223
Yeah, how come?

05:35.558 --> 05:37.123
Anything else?

05:37.125 --> 05:38.892
- No. No, I think we're good.
- No, thank you.

05:38.894 --> 05:40.193
All right then.
Whenever you're ready.

05:40.195 --> 05:41.495
Thank you. Sure.

05:41.497 --> 05:43.964
No, no! You gave me a lift.
This is the least I can do.

05:43.966 --> 05:47.036
- No, no, don't worry about it.
- Please, I insist.

05:56.212 --> 05:57.380
Thank you.

06:03.952 --> 06:08.087
So, uh, what did you say
you do? Sales?

06:08.089 --> 06:10.558
- Yeah.
- Like door-to-door?

06:10.560 --> 06:12.493
- Uh, no, no, no.
- Bible salesman?

06:12.495 --> 06:14.794
No, definitely not. No.

06:14.796 --> 06:15.830
I'm kidding.

06:15.832 --> 06:18.401
Uh... can I tell you something?

06:20.069 --> 06:22.736
I don't know
the first thing about sales.

06:22.738 --> 06:24.772
- Oh.
- I just made it up.

06:24.774 --> 06:26.907
Well, what do you do then?

06:26.909 --> 06:28.476
Well, that's a secret.

06:29.646 --> 06:31.344
- Oh, is it now?
- Yeah.

06:31.346 --> 06:32.580
And why is that?

06:32.582 --> 06:33.781
Well, because if I told you,

06:33.783 --> 06:35.048
you probably wouldn't want
to see me again.

06:35.050 --> 06:36.750
Who said
I was gonna see you again?

06:36.752 --> 06:38.288
Would you?

07:25.500 --> 07:27.000
This is...

07:27.002 --> 07:29.034
- You're not serious, are you?
- I am.

07:29.036 --> 07:31.203
- This is a joke.
- I'm serious.

07:31.205 --> 07:32.940
- Oh, come on.
- No, joke. No, it's no joke.

07:32.942 --> 07:34.877
Why would you
even tell me, then?

07:35.777 --> 07:37.546
Well, I think
because I trust you.

07:38.815 --> 07:40.115
You just met me.

07:40.849 --> 07:43.118
Well, sometimes
you just know is all.

07:43.918 --> 07:45.488
With me, you know?

07:46.688 --> 07:48.255
Well, you're still
sitting here.

07:48.257 --> 07:50.056
Well, that's because
I don't believe you.

07:50.058 --> 07:52.428
And if I did believe you...

07:53.728 --> 07:55.061
So, what'd be worse?

07:55.063 --> 07:57.399
If I'm lying about this
or telling you the truth?

08:02.771 --> 08:03.703
Prove it.

08:03.705 --> 08:05.238
- Prove it?
- Yeah.

08:05.240 --> 08:07.409
- You want me to prove it?
- Yeah.

08:08.444 --> 08:09.979
What'll you do if I can?

08:10.979 --> 08:12.548
I won't walk out that door.

08:19.822 --> 08:20.955
No, I'm not gonna do it.

08:20.957 --> 08:23.289
I didn't think so.

08:23.291 --> 08:24.459
Not because I can't.

08:25.661 --> 08:27.495
Because it's just
not my style.

08:27.497 --> 08:29.363
- Not your style?
- Mnh-mnh.

08:29.365 --> 08:30.763
- You have style?
- I do.

08:30.765 --> 08:33.668
Well, uh, tell me
what that is then.

08:33.669 --> 08:35.369
- My style?
- Yeah.

08:36.703 --> 08:39.041
Okay, well,
let's take this place.

08:40.075 --> 08:42.976
This place is not my style.

08:42.977 --> 08:44.447
Say it was a bank.

08:45.214 --> 08:46.813
And instead of that counter
up there,

08:46.815 --> 08:48.448
that was really
a teller's window.

08:48.450 --> 08:49.616
And that lady standing there

08:49.618 --> 08:51.519
was the teller
behind the window.

08:51.521 --> 08:53.886
And you just walk in,
real calm,

08:53.888 --> 08:55.255
and you'd find yourself a spot

08:55.257 --> 08:56.255
- and you'd sit down...
- Hold your horses!

08:56.257 --> 08:58.458
...just like we're sitting here.

08:58.460 --> 09:00.360
And you wait and you watch.

09:00.362 --> 09:01.962
And that may take
a couple of hours,

09:01.964 --> 09:03.731
might take
a couple of days, even.

09:03.733 --> 09:05.798
But you wait.
It's gotta feel right.

09:05.800 --> 09:07.168
The timing has to feel right.

09:07.170 --> 09:09.572
And when it does feel right,
you make your move.

09:11.006 --> 09:13.941
So you walk right up,
look her in the eye,

09:13.943 --> 09:17.178
and you say,
"Ma'am, this is a robbery."

09:17.180 --> 09:19.048
And you show her the gun,
like this.

09:19.781 --> 09:20.981
You say, "I want you
to fill that bag

09:20.983 --> 09:22.348
"with money,
hand it over to me.

09:22.350 --> 09:24.320
"And don't do anything stupid
or foolish.

09:25.054 --> 09:27.053
"I wouldn't want you
to get hurt.

09:27.055 --> 09:28.291
"'Cause I like you.

09:29.892 --> 09:30.993
"I like you a lot.

09:31.728 --> 09:35.095
"As a matter of fact, I might
even be falling for you,

09:35.097 --> 09:37.264
so don't go breaking
my heart now, okay."

09:38.367 --> 09:40.000
So, she'd fill up
the bag with money.

09:40.002 --> 09:41.202
She'd hand it over to me.

09:41.204 --> 09:42.903
And I'd go out
just the way I came in,

09:42.905 --> 09:44.638
real casual-like.

09:44.640 --> 09:45.942
And she'd...

09:47.575 --> 09:49.411
You tell me what she'd do?

09:57.752 --> 10:00.520
Hey. I'm just
pulling your leg.

10:34.523 --> 10:37.122
His hands were shaking.
That's what I kept noticing.

10:37.124 --> 10:39.592
His hands were shaking
all over the place.

10:39.594 --> 10:41.061
If he had pulled
that trigger,

10:41.063 --> 10:42.662
I don't even think he could
have pulled the trigger,

10:42.664 --> 10:43.996
he was so jacked up.

10:43.998 --> 10:44.731
But if he had, I...

10:44.733 --> 10:45.765
Nah. Nah. Nah.

10:45.767 --> 10:47.568
You did the right thing.

10:47.570 --> 10:48.637
How you feeling? You okay?

10:49.371 --> 10:51.741
Hey. Hey, John! John!

10:53.276 --> 10:55.042
I don't wanna make it
a big deal or nothing,

10:55.044 --> 10:56.175
but we all pitched in

10:56.177 --> 10:57.679
and got a little something
for you.

10:59.147 --> 11:02.082
Oh, shit.
The big 4-0.

11:02.084 --> 11:03.884
All downhill from here.

11:03.886 --> 11:05.221
Mm-hmm.

11:14.763 --> 11:17.599
We have to put all of
them in because Daddy's here.

11:21.237 --> 11:24.071
Happy birthday!

11:24.073 --> 11:27.274
Oh, man! What is this?

11:27.276 --> 11:29.576
- A surprise!
- Why didn't you tell me?

11:29.578 --> 11:32.612
Because then it wouldn't
have been a surprise!

11:32.614 --> 11:34.614
Cake for breakfast?

11:35.917 --> 11:38.217
Birthday cake for breakfast?

11:38.219 --> 11:40.220
Sweetheart,
whose idea was this?

11:40.222 --> 11:42.458
Oh, it was their idea.

11:48.030 --> 11:50.767
I tried telling them.

11:52.066 --> 11:54.101
Dad's going to be cranky,

11:54.103 --> 11:56.871
and he's not gonna want anyone
bringing up his age.

11:56.873 --> 11:58.105
"Dear Mr. President..."

11:58.107 --> 11:59.639
They said they didn't care.

11:59.641 --> 12:01.308
"...I was sorry to hear
that you got shot,

12:01.310 --> 12:03.943
and I'm happy to hear
that you're feeling better."

12:03.945 --> 12:05.111
What about you?

12:07.583 --> 12:09.084
It's your birthday.

12:10.151 --> 12:11.583
I'm not saying a thing.

12:11.585 --> 12:12.785
"I know
you probably can't tell me

12:12.787 --> 12:14.121
"because it's a secret,

12:14.123 --> 12:16.555
"but I bet there are
lots of them

12:16.557 --> 12:19.425
"and wonder if you play hide
and seek with the visitors.

12:19.427 --> 12:22.996
"I hope to visit some day
and think it would be fun.

12:22.998 --> 12:25.164
"Thank you
for making America safe.

12:25.166 --> 12:27.634
Yours truly, Abilene Hunt."

