13:12.047 --> 13:13.380
All right,
you wanna wait in the car

13:13.382 --> 13:14.448
or you wanna come in?

13:14.450 --> 13:15.848
- Come in.
- Wait.

13:15.850 --> 13:17.351
Can I have the keys
so I can listen to the radio?

13:17.353 --> 13:19.419
Yeah. And write
a note to your teacher

13:19.421 --> 13:21.722
because we're all
going to be late.

13:21.724 --> 13:22.757
Got it.

13:23.725 --> 13:24.759
Come on.

13:28.497 --> 13:30.900
Come on, buddy! 10-2.
Let's go!

14:19.247 --> 14:21.217
Who you praying to this time?

14:21.950 --> 14:24.016
Our Lady of, uh...

14:24.018 --> 14:26.886
Rare and Periodic Attendance.

14:30.191 --> 14:32.024
So, it's your choice,
all right?

14:32.026 --> 14:33.025
You gotta choose?

14:33.027 --> 14:34.193
Yeah!

14:34.195 --> 14:36.763
Okay, so then pick
whatever you want.

14:36.765 --> 14:38.531
I mean, you liked baseball,
didn't you?

14:38.533 --> 14:41.002
- Yeah.
- Okay, so pick baseball.

14:41.770 --> 14:44.004
Just pick
whatever you want to pick.

14:44.006 --> 14:45.405
That's... that's the most
important thing.

14:45.407 --> 14:47.140
Do the thing
that you want to do.

14:47.142 --> 14:49.076
But make sure that
you actually like it,

14:49.078 --> 14:50.177
you know what I mean?

14:50.179 --> 14:51.745
'Cause you're stuck with it.

14:51.747 --> 14:53.516
Why are you looking
at me like that?

14:56.384 --> 14:58.117
Do you like your job?

14:58.119 --> 15:00.953
Uh, excuse me, sir.
Can I see the manager?

15:00.955 --> 15:02.222
Well, that would be me.

15:02.224 --> 15:03.789
What can I do for you
this morning?

15:03.791 --> 15:05.725
Well, I'd like to ask
about a business loan.

15:05.727 --> 15:08.361
Well, sure. I bet
we can help you with that.

15:08.363 --> 15:11.334
Uh, what sort of business
are we talking about?

15:12.367 --> 15:14.067
Oh.

15:14.069 --> 15:15.671
This kind.

15:26.348 --> 15:27.683
Sit down.

15:29.718 --> 15:31.286
Dad, I'm bored.

15:32.054 --> 15:33.623
What do you want me to do?

15:39.895 --> 15:41.697
So, how are you feeling today?

15:43.398 --> 15:45.868
Not so good,
since you're asking.

15:47.335 --> 15:48.671
Well, the day's still young.

15:55.544 --> 15:57.313
I'm going
to give this to you.

15:58.347 --> 16:01.851
And what I want you to do
is fill it with money.

16:02.783 --> 16:04.150
You ever hear
about that frog

16:04.152 --> 16:05.619
that went to the bank
right there?

16:05.621 --> 16:06.653
No.

16:06.655 --> 16:08.690
A frog walked
into a bank one day.

16:09.891 --> 16:12.192
And he walks right up to
the teller. "May I speak..."

16:12.194 --> 16:14.026
Here they got a nameplate
and his name,

16:14.028 --> 16:16.261
it says Mr. Paddywhack on it.

16:16.263 --> 16:17.329
He walks up to him
and he says,

16:17.331 --> 16:18.731
"Excuse me, Mr. Paddywhack.

16:18.733 --> 16:20.833
"I'd like to talk to someone
about taking out a loan."

16:20.835 --> 16:23.605
And Mr. Paddywhack looked
at him and he said...

16:24.573 --> 16:26.809
"You can't get a loan.
You're just a frog."

16:27.542 --> 16:29.608
And the frog says,
"That doesn't seem fair.

16:29.610 --> 16:31.577
Would you go please speak
to your manager?"

16:31.579 --> 16:32.912
So Mr. Paddywhack went back

16:32.914 --> 16:35.314
and he talked to the manager
and he said...

16:35.316 --> 16:37.116
"Sir, there's a frog out there

16:37.118 --> 16:39.553
who's asking
about taking out a loan."

16:39.555 --> 16:41.587
And his, uh, manager said,

16:41.589 --> 16:43.591
"Well, does he have
any collateral?"

16:44.526 --> 16:47.659
Collateral is something
you can, uh, get if you're...

16:47.661 --> 16:50.333
hold on to to make sure that
people give their money back.

16:51.366 --> 16:53.766
And he said,
"I don't know. I'll go ask."

16:53.768 --> 16:54.903
And he sat down.

16:56.238 --> 16:58.270
He goes back out to the frog
and he says,

16:58.272 --> 16:59.675
"Do you have any collateral?"

17:01.310 --> 17:05.611
And, uh, the frog took out this
little teeny, tiny glass pear,

17:05.613 --> 17:07.781
and he puts it on the counter
and he said...

17:07.782 --> 17:10.684
"That glass pear is all
I have in the world."

17:10.685 --> 17:12.718
And then Mr. Paddywhack
takes it back

17:12.720 --> 17:14.021
to his manager and he says...

17:14.022 --> 17:16.589
So, we'll switch that
from checking to savings?

17:16.590 --> 17:19.059
"Sir, this is all
the frog has in the world."

17:19.060 --> 17:20.092
Thank you.

17:20.094 --> 17:21.227
The manager
looks at him,

17:21.229 --> 17:22.396
and he looks
at the little glass pear,

17:22.397 --> 17:23.766
and he says...

17:27.768 --> 17:30.269
He says, "It's a knick-knack,
Paddywhack.

17:30.271 --> 17:31.740
Give the frog a loan."

17:33.074 --> 17:35.342
