20:22.776 --> 20:26.278
both of which
I employ liberally and...

20:26.280 --> 20:27.882
We seem to get along
just fine.

20:28.784 --> 20:30.883
<i>Bueno para ti.</i>

20:30.885 --> 20:33.721
What am I supposed
to say to that? <i>Si?</i>

20:34.757 --> 20:37.957
<i>Si. Absolutamente.</i>

20:37.959 --> 20:40.860
Oh, man. I know
when I'm being made fun of,

20:40.862 --> 20:43.330
and I'm okay
with that because

20:43.332 --> 20:46.565
I've got a good sense
of humor about myself, sir.

20:46.567 --> 20:48.534
I've got a good sense
of humor about you, too.

20:48.536 --> 20:51.036
Yeah, right. Get the hell out.

20:51.038 --> 20:54.640
She wants me to take her...

20:54.642 --> 20:56.778
...down to Buenos Aires.

20:57.778 --> 20:59.345
- You ever been down there?
- Nope.

20:59.347 --> 21:02.180
Well, apparently they've got
some really good poetry.

21:02.182 --> 21:04.185
You're thinking of Chile.

21:05.621 --> 21:08.353
What's the difference?

21:08.355 --> 21:10.957
What about St. Louis?
You ever been to St. Louis?

21:10.959 --> 21:12.257
Sure.

21:12.259 --> 21:14.194
I got an idea for
a pretty good score up there.

21:14.196 --> 21:17.697
<i>...19 high school
ROTC cadets from Lubbock.</i>

21:17.699 --> 21:20.534
<i>The man put his charges to bed
