do you have in mind?

24:41.768 --> 24:43.438
This kind.

24:44.840 --> 24:46.108
This kind.

24:47.808 --> 24:49.476
This kind.

24:59.621 --> 25:00.621
This enough for you?

25:01.721 --> 25:03.257
Keep 'em coming,
please, Patty.

25:14.102 --> 25:16.138
God! Can I get some help?

25:17.605 --> 25:19.772
<i>Okay, what we have here
is five states.</i>

25:19.774 --> 25:21.373
- 93 robberies.
- In two years.

25:21.375 --> 25:23.342
And you think
it's all the same guys?

25:23.344 --> 25:24.310
Hundred percent.

25:24.312 --> 25:25.812
So, how do
the same three guys

25:25.814 --> 25:27.179
get away with all that?

25:27.181 --> 25:28.348
<i>Well, they haven't
gotten away with it.</i>

25:28.350 --> 25:30.216
<i>They just haven't
been caught yet.</i>

25:30.218 --> 25:31.551
<i>So, what do you want to do?</i>

25:31.553 --> 25:32.650
- What do we want to do?
- Yeah.

25:32.652 --> 25:33.585
We're going to catch 'em.

25:33.587 --> 25:34.589
We're going to catch 'em.

25:41.129 --> 25:42.164
Hello.

26:07.087 --> 26:10.258
Oh. You crying? Don't cry.

26:10.991 --> 26:12.659
What are you crying for?

26:12.661 --> 26:14.627
This is my first day.

26:14.629 --> 26:15.861
Well, there's always
a first time

26:15.863 --> 26:17.132
for everything, isn't there?

26:19.133 --> 26:20.134
Chin up.

26:22.769 --> 26:24.038
Okay.

26:25.506 --> 26:27.209
You're doing a great job.

26:34.114 --> 26:35.848
<i>And how would you
describe him?</i>

26:35.850 --> 26:38.921
Well, he was, uh...
he was very polite.

26:40.220 --> 26:42.988
He seemed like
a nice enough fella.

26:42.990 --> 26:45.257
- He was...
- Let me guess.

26:45.259 --> 26:48.561
- Uh, he was a gentleman.
- Well, yeah.

26:48.563 --> 26:50.265
But he was more...

26:51.665 --> 26:54.235
- He just seemed happy.
- Happy?

26:55.737 --> 26:57.005
Yeah.

26:57.972 --> 27:00.942
Did he look like either
of these two guys here?

27:02.411 --> 27:04.811
Yeah. Sorta. I gue...

27:04.813 --> 27:08.050
He... he just seemed more...

27:09.750 --> 27:11.085
Happy.

27:34.008 --> 27:35.309
Come on!

27:38.912 --> 27:40.446
It looks terrible now

27:40.448 --> 27:41.947
because I started
stripping the paper off

27:41.949 --> 27:43.181
thinking I'd change it.

27:43.183 --> 27:46.585
But then I found this
on the plaster...

27:46.587 --> 27:49.354
and I couldn't bring myself
to cover it up.

27:49.356 --> 27:52.057
I looked it up. That's the guy
that built this house.

27:52.059 --> 27:54.092
He signed that
about 100 years ago,

27:54.094 --> 27:55.730
and it's still there.

27:58.799 --> 28:01.133
Wiley here,
I've had since he was born

28:01.135 --> 28:03.101
and Clementine...

28:03.103 --> 28:04.469
Clementine belonged
to our neighbors,

28:04.471 --> 28:06.605
but she kept busting
through our fence.

28:06.607 --> 28:07.640
So, we...

28:07.642 --> 28:09.344
We finally just gave up
and bought her.

28:11.246 --> 28:14.813
So... all this
belongs to you, huh?

28:14.815 --> 28:16.549
Yup.

28:16.551 --> 28:18.186
- Wow.
- Me and the bank.

28:20.621 --> 28:21.821
Hmm.

28:21.823 --> 28:23.691
My kids keep telling me
to sell it,

28:24.725 --> 28:25.957
but I love it too much.

28:27.795 --> 28:29.461
They say
it's too expensive

28:29.463 --> 28:32.800
or that it's too much for me
to handle on my own, but...

28:33.901 --> 28:36.267
I say, well, come on out

28:36.269 --> 28:37.805
and give me a hand, then.

28:39.739 --> 28:41.175
I'm not going anywhere.

28:44.746 --> 28:46.148
You're not married, are ya?

28:46.948 --> 28:48.850
No... Me? No.

28:49.616 --> 28:51.819
I was once though.
That was when I was young.

28:53.054 --> 28:54.488
Got any kids?

28:56.356 --> 28:57.792
I hope not.

29:01.328 --> 29:02.995
- 75...
- Yeah.

29:02.997 --> 29:04.229
- ...76...
- Yes.

29:04.231 --> 29:05.296
- ...77...
- Yup.

29:05.298 --> 29:06.533
Can I have a sip of your beer?

29:06.535 --> 29:07.699
No. Go.

29:07.701 --> 29:11.003
78, 79, 80.

29:11.005 --> 29:13.104
80.
Okay, what comes after 80?

29:13.106 --> 29:14.540
- 81.
- 81.

29:14.542 --> 29:16.609
Now that's a trail.
You see a trail?

29:16.611 --> 29:17.543
Yeah.

29:17.545 --> 29:18.910
But where's the trail lead?

29:18.912 --> 29:20.213
The bad guy.

29:20.215 --> 29:21.550
To the bad guy.

29:22.350 --> 29:24.186
Now, where's
that bad guy going?

30:20.240 --> 30:22.610
Can we get two more coffees
over here, please?

30:25.046 --> 30:27.414
- How was the drive?
- Long.

30:28.216 --> 30:30.015
- Long.
- Romantic.

30:30.017 --> 30:32.554
Romantic?

30:34.421 --> 30:36.288
He didn't like
my book-on-tape.

31:19.866 --> 31:20.901
It's big.

31:23.871 --> 31:25.207
Real big.

31:28.442 --> 31:31.645
What I want to know is how
much they got in that truck.

31:38.952 --> 31:40.253
I'd like to talk to somebody

31:40.255 --> 31:41.823
about opening an IRA.

32:06.313 --> 32:08.647
Hi. Can you cash this
for me please?

32:08.649 --> 32:09.916
- Certainly.
- Thank you.

32:09.918 --> 32:11.386
- Will that be all?
- Yeah.

32:26.234 --> 32:27.399
I see all my friends
buying homes

32:27.401 --> 32:28.934
and doing
these grown up things

32:28.936 --> 32:31.773
that shouldn't have seemed
so big to me, but...

32:32.573 --> 32:33.773
when I'd add everything up,

32:33.775 --> 32:35.610
it just didn't make
any sense until...

32:36.844 --> 32:38.611
Oh, until now,

32:38.613 --> 32:40.178
and everything's
settled down...

32:41.315 --> 32:44.016
Sir. Sir, your cash.

32:44.018 --> 32:45.484
Oh. Thank you.

32:45.486 --> 32:47.055
...they're
in their right place.

32:48.956 --> 32:51.792
Oh, I'm a kid. My dad leaves.

32:52.526 --> 32:57.662
And when I turned a teenager,
my, uh, mom remarried.

32:57.664 --> 33:01.365
And she remarried
to a cop, so...

33:01.367 --> 33:04.035
- A cop?
- Christ, I know.

33:04.037 --> 33:07.605
I'm already doing petty crime
and that type of thing.

33:07.607 --> 33:09.507
Anyway, the first thing
he does is

33:09.509 --> 33:12.276
he changes all the locks
on the house.

33:12.278 --> 33:15.880
And, uh, and he writes
a 30-page manifesto

33:15.882 --> 33:20.252
about what's gonna happen
now that he's in charge.

33:20.254 --> 33:24.390
And things that we have to do,
things we can no longer do,

33:24.392 --> 33:25.658
that type of thing.

33:25.660 --> 33:27.226
Well, anyways,
it's Christmastime.

33:27.228 --> 33:29.829
I go out drinking,
I come home late.

33:29.831 --> 33:32.497
The house is locked up
like a federal prison.

33:32.499 --> 33:33.832
I...

33:33.834 --> 33:36.369
The only window available
to me is a high window,

33:36.371 --> 33:38.303
and I get up
into the high window

33:38.305 --> 33:39.737
and I get halfway through

33:39.739 --> 33:41.340
and I start losing my balance

33:41.342 --> 33:43.809
and I'm hanging on
to the Christmas tree.

33:43.811 --> 33:48.013
And the balls are falling
and the tinsels are tinseling.

33:48.015 --> 33:49.581
And I see through the tinsel,

33:49.583 --> 33:53.186
I see my stepfather
in his whitey-tighties

33:53.188 --> 33:55.254
in a combat position

33:55.256 --> 33:57.755
with both hands
on his revolver,

33:57.757 --> 34:00.492
and he's ready to squeeze
one off. And he says...

34:00.494 --> 34:04.763
"Freeze! Freeze, sailor!"

34:04.765 --> 34:07.332
He's never referred to me
as sailor before.

34:07.334 --> 34:09.368
It was a first.

34:09.370 --> 34:14.040
So I... Things got worse
from there and...

34:14.042 --> 34:15.810
And that's why
I hate Christmas.

34:22.449 --> 34:24.216
<i>- Hello?</i>
- Hey! It's me.

34:24.217 --> 34:25.484
<i>Oh, hello!</i>

34:25.485 --> 34:27.386
Is it too late for me to call?

34:27.388 --> 34:29.524
<i>No, it's...
it's not that late.</i>

34:30.857 --> 34:33.558
- So, what are you doing?
- <i>Just sitting at home,</i>

34:33.560 --> 34:36.428
<i>paying bills, procrastinating.</i>

34:36.429 --> 34:39.697
- Just waiting for me to call?
- <i>Careful, now.</i>

34:39.699 --> 34:41.234
<i>Where are you anyway?</i>

34:41.967 --> 34:45.170
Oh, somewhere in Oklahoma
or Missouri, I don't know.

34:45.172 --> 34:46.875
It all seems the same to me.

34:48.109 --> 34:51.746
So, you wanna come find me?

34:54.348 --> 34:55.947
So, the vault.

34:55.949 --> 34:58.685
- The vault and the truck.
- Hmm.

34:59.585 --> 35:01.620
You really think
we can do it?

35:01.622 --> 35:03.656
Yeah, I think
we can probably do it.

35:03.658 --> 35:05.991
We can probably do
anything we set our minds to.

35:05.993 --> 35:09.462
I'm just saying, it sounds
like we're showing off.

35:09.464 --> 35:11.496
Well, let's show off then.

35:11.498 --> 35:13.431
I'm so tired of doing
the same score

35:13.433 --> 35:15.132
over and over again.

35:15.134 --> 35:17.169
It's penny-ante bullshit.

35:17.171 --> 35:19.304
I'm gonna be 67 years old.

35:19.306 --> 35:20.841
My bones hurt.

35:22.243 --> 35:23.978
Jesus Christ.

35:25.846 --> 35:27.882
I'm gonna start thinking
about my future.

35:28.950 --> 35:30.051
My future.

35:31.852 --> 35:33.752
What are you thinking,
Forrest?

35:33.754 --> 35:35.856
Do you think
we can pull it off?

35:36.658 --> 35:39.093
- Yeah, probably.
- Probably?

35:40.194 --> 35:41.996
Probably?

35:43.163 --> 35:44.899
You forget about Paterson?

35:45.632 --> 35:47.433
Probably didn't get you
very far then.

35:47.435 --> 35:50.138
Yeah, but that was then.
This is now.

35:50.870 --> 35:53.272
And now,
I know what I'm doing.

35:53.274 --> 35:54.438
Yeah, I know, too.

35:54.440 --> 35:56.843
But I also know
what I'm capable of.

35:57.578 --> 36:00.946
And these days, those are
two different things.

36:02.216 --> 36:03.582
I don't have to calm down.

36:03.584 --> 36:04.984
No, don't touch me.

36:05.852 --> 36:07.286
I don't want to be cool.

36:07.288 --> 36:09.587
Just...
Would you be quiet?

36:09.589 --> 36:11.223
What is wrong
with my voice?

36:11.225 --> 36:12.424
What do I need
to be quiet for?

36:12.426 --> 36:15.729
You should take me home.
Your brother is...

36:16.564 --> 36:17.862
