try to touch someone's boobs?

36:21.201 --> 36:22.569
He's 13...

36:29.877 --> 36:31.277
<i>...controlled but caused</i>

36:31.279 --> 36:34.112
<i>heavy damage to the building
and its contents.</i>

36:34.114 --> 36:35.446
<i>The arson inspectors say</i>

36:35.448 --> 36:38.650
<i>there were several points
of instigation for the fire,</i>

36:38.652 --> 36:40.622
<i>and foul play
has not been ruled out.</i>

36:41.355 --> 36:42.922
<i>We now go to Dallas, Texas,</i>

36:42.924 --> 36:45.056
<i>where police from
multiple states have traced</i>

36:45.058 --> 36:47.725
<i>a series of dozens
of bank robberies</i>

36:47.727 --> 36:50.495
<i>to a band of
highly skilled robbers.</i>

36:50.497 --> 36:53.065
<i>Making this crime spree
even more unusual?</i>

36:53.067 --> 36:55.500
<i>These suspects are
a little bit older</i>

36:55.502 --> 36:57.236
<i>than your average criminals.</i>

36:57.238 --> 36:58.804
<i>Well,
we figure them to be about</i>

36:58.806 --> 37:00.437
<i>60 to 70 years old.</i>

37:00.439 --> 37:02.775
<i>For that reason, we're calling
them "The Over the Hill Gang."</i>

37:02.777 --> 37:04.676
<i>- Good name.
- Thank you.</i>

37:04.678 --> 37:06.178
<i>We came up with that.</i>

37:06.180 --> 37:07.446
<i>Folks from all around,</i>

37:07.448 --> 37:08.681
<i>some from Albuquerque
and Little Rock</i>

37:08.683 --> 37:09.781
<i>just putting
our heads together</i>

37:09.783 --> 37:11.516
<i>and hoping to nab
these guys.</i>

37:11.518 --> 37:12.984
<i>So, old men robbing banks,</i>

37:12.986 --> 37:14.920
<i>it seems like
they'd be fairly conspicuous.</i>

37:14.922 --> 37:17.589
<i>Any idea how they'd gotten
away with it for so long?</i>

37:17.591 --> 37:19.058
<i>Well, no.</i>

37:19.060 --> 37:20.725
<i>But frankly, they have
a whole lot more experience</i>

37:20.727 --> 37:22.761
<i>robbing banks than we do
catching them.</i>

37:22.763 --> 37:24.228
<i>Think you'll be
the one to catch 'em?</i>

37:24.230 --> 37:26.332
<i>Uh, I think
that any of these fellas here</i>

37:26.334 --> 37:28.766
<i>who put in long hours
and done some real hard work</i>

37:28.768 --> 37:30.301
<i>would like to do the job.</i>

37:30.303 --> 37:31.904
<i>But, yeah, I won't lie.</i>

37:31.906 --> 37:34.007
<i>I'd love to slap the cuffs
on them myself.</i>

37:35.676 --> 37:37.743
<i>I hope that happens.
I hope I get the chance.</i>

37:37.745 --> 37:39.111
<i>Here's hoping time
doesn't catch up with them</i>

37:39.113 --> 37:40.178
<i>before you do.</i>

37:40.180 --> 37:41.913
<i>- Okay, thank you.
- Thanks, Detective.</i>

37:41.915 --> 37:43.951
<i>- Thank you.
- Ted, back to you.</i>

37:50.957 --> 37:52.660
Hey, back already?

37:55.730 --> 37:57.362
You see the news?

37:57.364 --> 37:58.596
No.

37:58.598 --> 37:59.901
How's the weather?

38:01.201 --> 38:02.337
Blue skies.

38:15.082 --> 38:17.819
Hello?

38:25.326 --> 38:26.725
You gotta be kidding me.

38:40.942 --> 38:42.775
So, you can take
a look on the tapes.

38:42.777 --> 38:45.810
They just sweep right in,
lockstep with the guards.

38:45.812 --> 38:47.948
It's like they were escorting
them to the vaults.

38:50.084 --> 38:51.285
Detective?

38:52.719 --> 38:54.488
Detective Hunt?
We're this way.

38:55.455 --> 38:58.522
Um. Yeah, so, most people didn't
even know what was going on.

38:58.524 --> 38:59.924
- Is this John Hunt?
- Yeah.

38:59.926 --> 39:01.960
You're the talk
of the town, Detective.

39:01.962 --> 39:03.295
I gotta get
this straight. Okay.

39:03.297 --> 39:05.998
First, you followed them
into the street, right?

39:06.000 --> 39:07.466
Yes.

39:07.468 --> 39:09.301
And then you fired at them?

39:09.303 --> 39:11.737
Yeah. Like I said, two times.

39:11.739 --> 39:13.170
- Gold?
- Gold.

39:13.172 --> 39:14.406
Uh-huh.

39:14.408 --> 39:16.007
Well, what do you think
they're gonna do with gold?

39:16.009 --> 39:18.143
You tell me. And they'd have
gotten away scot-free

39:18.145 --> 39:20.114
except one of them stopped
to leave this.

39:23.850 --> 39:25.987
That is one hell
of a souvenir.

39:27.154 --> 39:31.125
They took off
one of my love handles.

39:33.227 --> 39:37.429
You know, I never actually
finished medical school.

39:37.431 --> 39:38.763
Come on.
Come on. Come on.

39:38.765 --> 39:40.598
Don't tell me that, boy.

39:49.176 --> 39:50.674
<i>We have some breaking news</i>

39:50.676 --> 39:52.143
<i>to tell you about right now.</i>

39:52.145 --> 39:54.712
<i>Police are looking
for three suspects</i>

39:54.714 --> 39:57.047
<i>who attempted to rob
First Nation's Bank...</i>

39:59.352 --> 40:00.851
How are you doing?

40:00.853 --> 40:02.924
Huh? I'm all right.

40:05.893 --> 40:08.096
We almost did it, didn't we?

40:09.428 --> 40:11.064
No, we did do it.

40:21.341 --> 40:23.009
<i>What are we
looking for here?</i>

40:25.480 --> 40:27.578
Stop right there.
Stop it. Go back.

40:27.580 --> 40:28.781
Wait till the guards go past.

40:28.783 --> 40:29.948
No, no. It's there.
It's there.

40:29.950 --> 40:31.783
You're moving forward.
Go back.

40:31.785 --> 40:33.585
It's slow motion.
It takes a second.

40:33.587 --> 40:35.120
You got to rewind it.

40:35.122 --> 40:36.187
It's rewinding.

40:36.189 --> 40:37.790
- You're going forward.
- There you go, see.

40:37.792 --> 40:38.857
Come on, man. Just push...

40:38.859 --> 40:40.326
You're not even...
you're pushing...

40:40.328 --> 40:42.361
- It's this one. Stop! Stop!
- Go back to where it was.

40:42.363 --> 40:44.730
Don't stop on an empty frame!
Stop on his face.

40:44.732 --> 40:46.434
There! Right there.
Stop right there.

40:48.602 --> 40:49.970
Look at that.

40:52.739 --> 40:54.408
Is he smiling?

40:55.875 --> 40:57.341
Must be thinkin' of you.

40:59.446 --> 41:01.082
- Detective Hunt?
- Yeah.

41:01.814 --> 41:03.150
Those the guys?

41:04.685 --> 41:05.949
Yeah.

41:05.951 --> 41:09.189
Hmm. Well, we're going
to need those tapes.

41:10.424 --> 41:12.089
These tapes are my evidence.

41:12.091 --> 41:14.592
Not any longer they're not.
It's a federal case now.

41:14.594 --> 41:15.995
Thank you very much.

41:16.930 --> 41:18.129
<i>You know,
the Bureau was actually</i>

41:18.131 --> 41:20.297
<i>put together
to catch guys like these.</i>

41:20.299 --> 41:21.165
Mm-hmm.

41:21.167 --> 41:23.234
There was Dillinger. Who else?

41:23.236 --> 41:25.872
Well, Dillinger and a bunch
of other guys like him.

41:26.674 --> 41:28.940
Point is,
you've done your part, John.

41:28.942 --> 41:31.011
You did a good job.

41:32.379 --> 41:33.946
Right.

41:33.948 --> 41:35.647
Hard part's over.

41:35.649 --> 41:37.919
Now's the part where
we bring this home.

41:40.187 --> 41:41.322
Mmm.

41:42.422 --> 41:44.591
Yeah? That could be.

41:45.593 --> 41:47.094
You could bring this home.

41:48.828 --> 41:50.995
Or it could be that
I puzzle things together.

41:50.997 --> 41:52.299
I find that clue.

41:53.234 --> 41:54.368
I crack the case.

41:55.167 --> 41:57.969
And maybe you come
to me and you say,

41:57.971 --> 41:59.536
"Thanks, John.
Let me shake your hand.

41:59.538 --> 42:02.509
"You puzzled things together.
You cracked the case.

42:04.310 --> 42:05.478
That's good work."

42:09.149 --> 42:10.317
You remember something?

42:11.285 --> 42:13.321
Uhh...

42:15.156 --> 42:16.224
No.

42:18.325 --> 42:20.891
But they want
the same thing you want.

42:20.893 --> 42:23.129
Yeah, that's true.

42:24.131 --> 42:26.498
So, why don't they
just let you do it?

42:26.500 --> 42:29.070
They think
that they can do it better.

42:29.904 --> 42:31.105
Can they?

42:32.439 --> 42:33.574
Probably.

42:41.647 --> 42:43.316
Can you get a tire iron, bud?

42:45.018 --> 42:46.884
Maybe it's a good thing.

42:46.886 --> 42:48.754
How's it a good thing?

42:48.756 --> 42:50.522
Because they aren't
as good as you are.

42:50.524 --> 42:51.790
So they won't catch him.

42:51.792 --> 42:53.558
Well, thank you, babe.

42:53.560 --> 42:54.926
And if it was your job,

42:54.928 --> 42:56.364
you would definitely
catch him.

42:57.163 --> 42:59.498
But that's why it's good
that you're not.

42:59.500 --> 43:00.866
Because if you caught him,

43:00.868 --> 43:02.603
you wouldn't get
to chase him anymore.

43:06.172 --> 43:07.941
I like how you think.

43:31.799 --> 43:33.334
That's that, isn't it?

43:35.835 --> 43:37.405
I'll be seeing you boys.

43:38.272 --> 43:39.674
Take care, Teddy.

43:44.812 --> 43:46.547
Say, I...

43:48.147 --> 43:51.419
Somethin' I've been meaning
to ask you and, uh...

43:53.687 --> 43:56.656
You got a place across
the street from a cemetery.

43:59.058 --> 44:00.792
For a reason?

44:00.794 --> 44:02.393
No.

44:02.395 --> 44:03.698
No. Okay.

44:05.565 --> 44:06.634
Okay.

44:07.901 --> 44:09.833
You really
never thought about it?

44:09.835 --> 44:11.339
No, not really.

44:12.872 --> 44:15.008
Okay. All right.

44:17.944 --> 44:19.243
I'll see you next week.

44:19.245 --> 44:23.383
And think
about laying low, okay.

44:24.317 --> 44:27.520
- All right.
- Bye, Forrest.

44:45.806 --> 44:47.041
John?

44:47.975 --> 44:50.578
Come on, John.
Don't look so sad, man.

44:51.911 --> 44:53.111
We don't need
to waste our time

44:53.113 --> 44:55.382
on a bunch
of old folks anyhow.

45:12.366 --> 45:13.366
What's that?

45:17.138 --> 45:18.372
Nothing.

45:34.087 --> 45:35.920
You sure
you don't want to try?

45:35.922 --> 45:37.290
Maybe next time.

45:38.091 --> 45:39.757
Thought this was
on your list?

45:39.759 --> 45:41.227
Oh, it still is.

45:43.062 --> 45:45.365
Come on. Come on.

45:49.136 --> 45:52.036
- So, do you miss him?
- Oh, sure.

45:52.038 --> 45:54.071
But we got married
when we were young.

45:54.073 --> 45:55.373
Like you did.

45:55.375 --> 45:58.079
And then the kids came and...

45:59.145 --> 46:02.115
Oh, you could kind of lose
track of yourself, you know.

46:03.984 --> 46:05.317
At least I do.

46:06.185 --> 46:08.353
And it's so easy to assume
that everything's fine.

46:08.355 --> 46:09.920
That this is fine.
This is the way

46:09.922 --> 46:11.091
things are supposed to be.

46:11.825 --> 46:15.192
And so, you spend so much time
thinking you're happy,

46:15.194 --> 46:16.627
and then one day you wake up
and you realize,

46:16.629 --> 46:19.667
oh, maybe you aren't.

46:21.000 --> 46:23.169
Maybe you never were
in the first place.

46:24.904 --> 46:27.707
Maybe you don't
even know what that means.

46:29.308 --> 46:32.611
Then something happens,
like you lose someone or...

46:33.379 --> 46:35.647
even your kids grow up
and leave home,

46:35.649 --> 46:37.118
and you think...

46:38.352 --> 46:40.120
"What do I have left?"

46:40.853 --> 46:42.687
So, yeah, I miss him.

46:42.689 --> 46:45.522
And there's a part of me
that always will, but...

46:45.524 --> 46:49.629
now I think,
now it's okay to be selfish.

46:51.732 --> 46:53.098
'Cause you think about...

46:53.100 --> 46:54.866
ten years from now,
where will you be?

46:54.868 --> 46:55.969
What'll you be doing?

46:56.703 --> 46:59.337
Now, whenever I close
the door, I think...

46:59.339 --> 47:01.239
"Oh, at least this is
the last time

47:01.241 --> 47:02.973
"I'll ever have
a chance to do

47:02.975 --> 47:04.678
whatever that thing was?"

47:05.444 --> 47:07.446
You know what I do
when the door closes?

47:07.448 --> 47:09.681
- What's that?
- I jump out the window.

47:12.951 --> 47:14.152
And look, if I ever wonder

47:14.154 --> 47:15.420
what I'm doing
or where I'm going,

47:15.422 --> 47:17.288
I just think of myself
as that little kid I was

47:17.290 --> 47:18.790
when I was just about
this tall.

47:18.792 --> 47:20.290
And I say, well...

47:20.292 --> 47:22.262
now would he have been
proud of me?

47:23.296 --> 47:25.029
And if the answer is no,

47:25.031 --> 47:27.265
well, then I just
keep walking on through.

47:27.267 --> 47:30.134
But if the answer is yes,
then I know I'm exactly

47:30.136 --> 47:31.639
where I'm supposed to be.

47:34.707 --> 47:37.544
So, is he proud of ya?
That little boy?

47:39.279 --> 47:41.379
Oh, he's getting closer
every day.

47:41.381 --> 47:44.649
But you're never exactly where
you're supposed to be, are ya?

47:44.651 --> 47:46.784
I mean, 'cause if you are,
you're dead.

47:49.790 --> 47:52.658
And a little 10-year-old you.
He's...

47:52.660 --> 47:55.228
You know, he might have hopes
and dreams, but...

47:57.129 --> 47:58.965
he doesn't understand time...

47:59.899 --> 48:01.401
or the world like you do.

48:03.002 --> 48:04.270
So...

48:06.705 --> 48:09.174
Think you gotta
keep on keeping on.

48:09.176 --> 48:12.909
Just living your life.
Trying new things.

48:12.911 --> 48:16.549
Just gotta...
keep on pushing.

48:35.435 --> 48:36.837
Uh, ma'am, excuse me.

48:37.571 --> 48:39.670
I would like to speak
to the manager.

48:39.672 --> 48:42.008
Yes, that's me.
What can I do for you?

48:43.176 --> 48:46.877
Okay, so you want
to take over the mortgage?

48:46.879 --> 48:49.950
I do. I'd like to pay
for it all upfront.

48:50.718 --> 48:52.417
Well, that can
certainly be done,

48:52.419 --> 48:55.053
but she would need to come in
and sign over the...

48:55.055 --> 48:56.855
Well, I'd like it
to be a surprise.

48:56.857 --> 48:58.190
Oh, I see.

48:58.192 --> 48:59.824
See, I give you the money...

48:59.826 --> 49:02.395
and then she didn't necessarily
have to know about it.

49:03.196 --> 49:05.096
Well, that's a heck
of a Christmas present.

49:06.232 --> 49:07.399
So, you have a few options.

49:07.401 --> 49:10.667
One is you could make
a gift to her.

49:10.669 --> 49:12.703
The other is
she could come in

49:12.705 --> 49:14.138
and sign the property
over to you.

49:14.140 --> 49:16.074
No, no, no.
I don't want to do that.

49:16.076 --> 49:17.641
I just want to pay
for it all

49:17.643 --> 49:19.877
and not have her
necessarily know about it.

49:19.879 --> 49:22.048
Well, she'll know
one way or another.

49:24.216 --> 49:26.319
But what if I had
the money here?

49:27.254 --> 49:28.786
- Right now?
- Yes.

49:28.788 --> 49:31.725
- You have it?
- No, but what if I did?

49:32.625 --> 49:34.125
She'd still need to come in

49:34.127 --> 49:35.592
and sign off
on some paperwork.

49:35.594 --> 49:36.560
I see.

49:36.562 --> 49:37.929
I-It would be very easy.

49:37.931 --> 49:39.230
Just a quick bit of paperwork.

49:39.232 --> 49:41.065
Yeah. Just not
right now though.

49:41.067 --> 49:42.866
No.

49:42.868 --> 49:46.806
Okay, well... thank you.

50:30.750 --> 50:31.919
Thank you.

50:37.658 --> 50:39.223
<i>Is it all right
if I call you Dorothy?</i>

50:39.225 --> 50:40.757
<i>Dot.
You can call me Dot.</i>

50:40.759 --> 50:42.659
<i>All right. I'm going
to record this conversation</i>

50:42.661 --> 50:45.399
<i>- if that's all right with you.
- Okay.</i>

50:46.332 --> 50:48.434
So...

50:49.770 --> 50:51.905
why don't you just tell me
what you remember?

50:53.239 --> 50:55.142
Okay. Um...

50:56.243 --> 50:58.076
Well...

50:58.078 --> 50:59.310
Wait, I'm sorry.
Hang on a second.

50:59.312 --> 51:00.645
It's okay.

51:00.647 --> 51:03.016
I don't usually do the...

51:04.283 --> 51:05.718
You made it worse.

51:10.455 --> 51:12.725
- There we go. All right. Yup.
- It's okay?

51:13.660 --> 51:15.696
Sorry about that. So, uh...

51:16.529 --> 51:18.763
- Should I start again?
- Yeah.

51:18.765 --> 51:23.234
Okay. Um... Gosh.

51:23.236 --> 51:26.904
Well, he and my mom
were only together

51:26.906 --> 51:30.208
for two years, so...

51:30.210 --> 51:33.781
I never met him
that I can recall.

51:35.314 --> 51:37.949
By the time I was born,
he was...

51:37.951 --> 51:39.186
already in prison.

51:40.520 --> 51:42.687
My brother says that he...
he thinks

51:42.689 --> 51:44.355
he can remember him
a little bit,

51:44.357 --> 51:48.025
but I don't know
if he really does...

51:48.027 --> 51:50.763
or if he just thinks
he does 'cause...

51:51.564 --> 51:53.931
You know how it is.
You hear a story and...

51:53.933 --> 51:56.366
you see a picture
and you kind of put

51:56.368 --> 51:57.904
two and two together.

51:58.872 --> 52:01.007
And we heard
all kinds of stories.

52:01.808 --> 52:04.574
She told us all kinds
of stories about him.

52:04.576 --> 52:08.045
And they didn't really
add up,

52:08.047 --> 52:10.882
but we were just kids, so...

52:10.884 --> 52:15.622
He was off sailing
the high seas one year and...

52:16.756 --> 52:18.556
- I think he was off to war...
- Big stories.

52:18.558 --> 52:20.824
- Yeah. Exactly.
- All right. Okay.

52:20.826 --> 52:23.094
Didn't really make
any difference.

52:23.096 --> 52:24.832
He was just dad and...

52:25.564 --> 52:28.200
he was doing stuff and...

52:29.035 --> 52:32.172
someday he was gonna
come back and see us.

52:33.806 --> 52:35.573
And then, um...

52:35.575 --> 52:38.942
...I think I was 15 and, uh...

52:38.944 --> 52:41.712
I guess he was
gonna be paroled, so...

52:41.714 --> 52:45.886
my mom, she sat us down
and told us the truth.

52:47.018 --> 52:50.656
Just in case he came
looking for us, but...

52:52.024 --> 52:53.958
Well, he never did, so...

52:53.960 --> 52:56.393
And so he never called you?
He never wrote?

52:56.395 --> 52:58.228
- Oh, no.
- Mm-hmm.

52:58.230 --> 53:00.066
No. No, he didn't. Uh...

53:00.801 --> 53:03.701
I guess for all I know,
he doesn't know I exist.

53:08.908 --> 53:10.475
And he's a grandpa.

53:10.477 --> 53:12.710
Yeah, I guess he is.

53:12.712 --> 53:14.982
- What's his name?
- Oh, that's Robbie.

53:15.982 --> 53:17.848
Robbie, sweetheart,
you want to say hi?

53:17.850 --> 53:19.085
- No.
- No?

53:19.919 --> 53:22.022
- Sorry.
- No, that's all right.

53:24.457 --> 53:26.223
I got a boy
just about his age.

53:29.529 --> 53:31.698
So, you think
you're gonna catch him?

53:32.632 --> 53:33.931
Well, I hope so.

53:33.933 --> 53:35.768
Well, if you do,
I don't wanna see him.

53:36.701 --> 53:37.835
I don't wanna have to come in

53:37.837 --> 53:39.636
and pick him out of...
what's it...

53:39.638 --> 53:42.239
a lineup
or whatever it's called, okay.

53:42.241 --> 53:43.977
No, that won't be necessary.

53:44.944 --> 53:46.947
You know, I think
he should be locked up.

53:48.915 --> 53:50.750
You know,
my momma told me that...

53:51.651 --> 53:53.217
he always said...

53:53.219 --> 53:55.988
"Oh, I'm a changed man now."

53:57.223 --> 53:58.422
And then he would just get out

53:58.424 --> 54:00.627
and he'd just do it
all over again.

54:01.460 --> 54:03.296
And again and again.

54:05.730 --> 54:07.130
Even after all that, you know,

54:07.132 --> 54:09.770
she loved him
till the day she died.

54:24.317 --> 54:25.585
How about this guy?

54:26.386 --> 54:27.752
That's beautiful.

54:27.754 --> 54:29.520
Oh, it's too much money.

54:29.522 --> 54:31.321
What about something...

54:31.323 --> 54:32.589
How about this one?

54:32.591 --> 54:34.025
I love this piece.

54:37.330 --> 54:39.210
- Would you like to try it on?
- I would.

54:44.036 --> 54:45.272
Oh.

54:47.473 --> 54:49.742
Oh. Take your time.

54:50.609 --> 54:52.078
What do you think?

54:55.614 --> 54:57.250
Let's see it
in the light here.

55:49.935 --> 55:54.638
Oh, I am so embarrassed!
I just walked right off.

55:54.640 --> 55:57.176
I felt so... I'm so sorry!

55:57.944 --> 55:59.375
Would you like me
to help you take it off?

55:59.377 --> 56:01.080
No. Um...

56:02.248 --> 56:03.350
I'll take it.

56:04.984 --> 56:08.989
- How much?
- $249.99 with tax.

56:19.832 --> 56:22.533
Yeah, I held on
to all of this stuff.

56:22.535 --> 56:24.768
Back when I represented him...

56:24.770 --> 56:28.138
I thought maybe I'd write
a book or something like that

56:28.140 --> 56:30.341
or maybe even just tell
my grandkids about it.

56:30.343 --> 56:31.777
It's such a great story.

56:39.051 --> 56:40.786
Is that the man
you're looking for?

56:41.520 --> 56:43.654
Yeah, I do believe it is.

56:43.656 --> 56:44.855
Man, I remember
Forrest Tucker.

56:44.857 --> 56:46.359
He was the real deal.

56:48.160 --> 56:49.462
Holy smokes.

56:50.797 --> 56:52.895
Age 13, bicycle theft.

56:52.897 --> 56:54.300
That's getting an early start.

56:55.067 --> 56:56.902
He spent
his whole life locked up.

56:57.736 --> 57:00.337
Except for the times
that he broke out.

57:00.339 --> 57:03.473
Sixteen successful escapes.

57:03.475 --> 57:04.808
- Sixteen?
- Uh-huh.

57:04.810 --> 57:06.643
That's some kind
of record, right?

57:06.645 --> 57:12.118
A few years back, he broke out
of San Quentin in a boat...

57:12.986 --> 57:15.286
he built out
of scrap wood and tarp

57:15.288 --> 57:17.154
and who knows what else.

57:17.156 --> 57:19.623
Painted the Marin County logo
on the side

57:19.625 --> 57:21.460
and sailed
right on out of there.

57:22.728 --> 57:25.096
You ever meet him,
he'll tell you all about it.

57:25.098 --> 57:28.299
He'll tell you every detail
of every adventure he ever had.

57:28.301 --> 57:29.933
And probably a few
that he didn't.

57:29.935 --> 57:31.034
Maybe somebody
should have told him

57:31.036 --> 57:32.506
to quit while he was ahead.

57:33.239 --> 57:35.408
Well, you find something
you love.

57:36.276 --> 57:39.143
<i>I got put on his case when
he got caught in Montana</i>

57:39.145 --> 57:41.679
<i>a few years back.</i>

57:41.681 --> 57:43.346
There was a chase...

57:43.348 --> 57:47.153
which I learned
was not unusual at all.

57:48.154 --> 57:49.819
Well, when they got
to the showdown,

57:49.821 --> 57:52.457
the cops said
that he fired on them.

57:53.459 --> 57:56.761
But he claimed that, uh,
he didn't even have a gun.

57:56.763 --> 57:59.163
That it was just
his car backfiring.

57:59.165 --> 58:01.301
I expect
that's probably half true.

58:02.602 --> 58:04.067
He did always have
a gun on him,

58:04.069 --> 58:06.971
but if you told me that
he had never fired that thing

58:06.973 --> 58:09.075
once in his life,
I'd believe ya.

58:09.942 --> 58:12.109
I remember
I sat down with him once

58:12.111 --> 58:13.513
and I said, "Forrest...

58:15.448 --> 58:18.016
"surely there's an easier way

58:18.018 --> 58:20.884
for somebody in your position
to make a living."

58:20.886 --> 58:23.254
And he looked at me
and he said, "Brother...

58:23.256 --> 58:25.926
"I'm not talking about
making a living.

58:26.792 --> 58:28.929
I'm just talking
about living."

59:11.437 --> 59:13.939
<i>Keep your
hands where I can see 'em!</i>

59:15.841 --> 59:17.643
<i>Better not be crossed.</i>

01:01:04.049 --> 01:01:05.317
Hi, baby.

01:01:06.319 --> 01:01:07.319
Hi.

01:01:08.853 --> 01:01:10.721
Did you find him?

01:01:10.723 --> 01:01:12.325
Yeah, sorta.

01:01:13.426 --> 01:01:14.627
What's that mean?

01:01:16.562 --> 01:01:17.764
Well...

01:01:18.763 --> 01:01:21.230
I figured out who he is.

01:01:21.232 --> 01:01:22.267
And?

01:01:25.872 --> 01:01:28.672
He's a guy who is old...

01:01:28.674 --> 01:01:30.142
but used to be young.

01:01:32.044 --> 01:01:35.347
And he just loves
robbing banks.

01:01:37.649 --> 01:01:39.285
- That's it?
- That's it.

01:01:41.020 --> 01:01:44.254
Just like you're a guy
who's a cop...

01:01:44.256 --> 01:01:45.724
who's gonna catch him.

01:01:53.598 --> 01:01:56.502
Yeah. Something like that.

01:02:01.439 --> 01:02:03.841
It's late.

01:02:04.676 --> 01:02:07.379
- It's not that late, baby.
- The kids are asleep.

01:02:09.547 --> 01:02:11.051
How asleep are they?

01:02:11.783 --> 01:02:14.752
Oh, my goodness.

01:02:14.754 --> 01:02:16.821
- Come on. Let's go out.
- What?

01:02:16.823 --> 01:02:18.288
Let's go out.
Let's get a babysitter.

01:02:18.290 --> 01:02:20.089
I have to work in the morning.

01:02:20.091 --> 01:02:21.760
- So what?
- What?

01:02:25.064 --> 01:02:27.297
- What is going on with you?
- I don't know.

01:02:30.368 --> 01:02:32.937
Wait, shouldn't you be
calling somebody?

01:02:32.939 --> 01:02:34.837
But shouldn't... No.
Telling who?

01:02:34.839 --> 01:02:36.105
That you found him?

01:02:36.107 --> 01:02:38.375
Tell who? Tell them?
I'm not telling anybody.

01:02:39.978 --> 01:02:41.647
Tonight he's all mine.

01:03:26.459 --> 01:03:27.493
Hey.

01:03:28.426 --> 01:03:29.560
Yeah.

01:03:29.562 --> 01:03:32.462
You really just
drifted off into outer space.

01:03:34.000 --> 01:03:36.900
Yeah. Hey, you wanna
get out of here?

01:03:36.902 --> 01:03:38.234
Oh, we just ordered pie.

01:03:38.236 --> 01:03:39.335
No, I mean
really get out of here.

01:03:39.337 --> 01:03:40.739
Like take a trip somewhere.

01:03:42.174 --> 01:03:44.677
- Like a vacation?
- Yeah.

01:03:45.844 --> 01:03:48.411
Oh. I don't know, I...

01:03:48.413 --> 01:03:50.681
You know, I've got the animals
to take care of and...

01:03:50.683 --> 01:03:53.219
Yeah, but say that wasn't
a problem. Would you want to?

01:03:55.453 --> 01:03:56.620
Maybe.

01:03:56.622 --> 01:03:57.623
Okay.

01:04:22.281 --> 01:04:23.682
Hey!

01:04:25.817 --> 01:04:27.586
Didn't I see you on TV?

01:04:34.893 --> 01:04:36.326
- Oh, maybe.
- No, I think so.

01:04:36.328 --> 01:04:37.426
You were involved in that...
What were you call...

01:04:37.428 --> 01:04:38.931
The Over The Hill Gang, right?

01:04:40.065 --> 01:04:41.165
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

01:04:41.167 --> 01:04:42.435
Did you catch them?

01:04:45.703 --> 01:04:46.837
Not yet.

01:04:46.839 --> 01:04:48.875
Hmm. You close?

01:04:49.908 --> 01:04:51.210
Oh, we're getting there.

01:04:52.511 --> 01:04:54.911
Excuse me. I don't want
to be rude here, but...

01:04:54.913 --> 01:04:56.513
straighten this out
a little bit.

01:04:56.515 --> 01:04:59.350
I was forced to learn how
to do this in Catholic school.

01:04:59.352 --> 01:05:01.054
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

01:05:01.955 --> 01:05:04.824
There you go. Looking sharp.
You got a gal with you?

01:05:05.924 --> 01:05:07.524
I got my wife with me, yeah.

01:05:07.526 --> 01:05:09.326
Oh, this is great.

01:05:09.328 --> 01:05:11.060
It's been my experience
that looking sharp

01:05:11.062 --> 01:05:12.328
will take you a long,
long way.

01:05:12.330 --> 01:05:14.130
Make you look like you know
what you're doing.

01:05:14.933 --> 01:05:16.236
Even if you don't.

01:05:20.772 --> 01:05:21.841
Forrest?

01:05:26.245 --> 01:05:27.680
I know what I'm doing.

01:07:09.281 --> 01:07:10.516
Goodnight.

01:09:56.782 --> 01:09:58.615
<i>Forrest Tucker,
you are under arrest.</i>

01:09:58.617 --> 01:10:00.249
<i>Step away from the car!</i>

01:10:00.251 --> 01:10:03.154
<i>Put your hands up and
step away from the car now!</i>

01:10:05.890 --> 01:10:08.092
<i>Don't do it!
Get out of the car!</i>

01:10:57.975 --> 01:11:00.209
<i>Two cars south bound on...</i>

01:11:00.211 --> 01:11:02.848
<i>FS-522 going south bound...</i>

01:11:33.310 --> 01:11:34.613
Please.

01:11:35.480 --> 01:11:38.184
Please. My boy.

01:11:49.694 --> 01:11:50.694
Okay.

01:11:50.696 --> 01:11:51.928
Pull over here.

01:13:55.953 --> 01:13:57.288
Is he okay?

01:13:59.157 --> 01:14:00.192
Mm-hmm.

01:14:01.493 --> 01:14:02.928
I understand.

01:14:04.830 --> 01:14:07.466
Okay, well.
Hey, thanks for calling.

01:14:10.102 --> 01:14:11.634
All right.

01:14:22.447 --> 01:14:24.948
What happened?

01:14:24.950 --> 01:14:26.285
Well, they caught him.

01:14:27.786 --> 01:14:29.421
- They did?
- Yeah.

01:14:31.290 --> 01:14:32.892
- Yup.
- How?

01:14:34.292 --> 01:14:37.897
Oh, somebody talked.

01:14:39.364 --> 01:14:40.866
Hmm.

01:14:42.800 --> 01:14:44.135
Now what?

01:14:45.604 --> 01:14:47.006
He'll go to prison.

01:14:47.872 --> 01:14:49.140
Hmm.

01:14:50.408 --> 01:14:51.876
That's too bad.

01:14:53.577 --> 01:14:55.046
Yeah, I guess so.

01:14:59.518 --> 01:15:01.554
I'm sorry
you didn't catch him.

01:15:07.692 --> 01:15:09.060
I'm not.

01:15:25.609 --> 01:15:28.779
<i>The Over
the Hill Gang is no more.</i>

01:15:28.781 --> 01:15:31.147
<i>Last night,
federal agents in Fort Worth</i>

01:15:31.149 --> 01:15:33.016
<i>arrested the leader
of the group,</i>

01:15:33.018 --> 01:15:36.552
<i>74-year-old
Forrest Silver Tucker.</i>

01:15:36.554 --> 01:15:38.286
<i>Tucker, a native of Florida,</i>

01:15:38.288 --> 01:15:41.022
<i>is best remembered in the
Bay area for engineering...</i>

01:15:41.024 --> 01:15:42.491
<i>...one of the most</i>

01:15:42.493 --> 01:15:44.793
<i>innovative prison breaks
in San Quentin history.</i>

01:15:44.795 --> 01:15:47.097
<i>That is just one
of a long list of escapes</i>

01:15:47.099 --> 01:15:49.833
<i>and an even longer list
of crimes.</i>

01:16:11.688 --> 01:16:14.091
<i>But after
a few years on the lam,</i>

01:16:14.093 --> 01:16:16.959
<i>time has officially caught up
with this career criminal.</i>

01:16:16.961 --> 01:16:20.195
<i>Also arrested,
fellow convict Teddy Green</i>

01:16:20.197 --> 01:16:22.266
<i>whom Tucker met
in San Quentin.</i>

01:16:22.268 --> 01:16:25.035
<i>A third member of the gang
is still at large,</i>

01:16:25.037 --> 01:16:27.271
<i>but for the time being,
police say</i>

01:16:27.273 --> 01:16:30.576
<i>The Over the Hill Gang
is officially retired.</i>

01:17:02.072 --> 01:17:04.209
Forrest Tucker,
you got a visitor.

01:17:12.983 --> 01:17:15.254
You lied to me
about your name.

01:17:16.920 --> 01:17:18.589
Well, I figured you knew.

01:17:20.125 --> 01:17:23.261
That's what the detectives
asked me, if I knew.

01:17:24.862 --> 01:17:29.400
If I even had
the slightest idea.

01:17:30.167 --> 01:17:33.471
- Hmm, what'd you say?
- Said of course not.

01:17:36.675 --> 01:17:38.607
I'm sorry.

01:17:38.609 --> 01:17:40.679
Well, me too.

01:17:47.051 --> 01:17:49.188
Here. I wrote something
for you.

01:17:57.696 --> 01:17:59.061
What's this?

01:17:59.063 --> 01:18:01.499
These are all the times
I broke out before.

01:19:46.304 --> 01:19:47.469
You coming, Forrest?

01:19:47.471 --> 01:19:48.905
Oh, I'm gonna finish up here.

01:19:48.907 --> 01:19:50.309
I'll be with you in a minute.

01:19:51.608 --> 01:19:52.743
Okay.

01:20:45.796 --> 01:20:46.831
What about this one?

01:20:47.931 --> 01:20:48.934
Well...

01:20:50.167 --> 01:20:52.336
kinda saving
the best for last.

01:20:55.206 --> 01:20:56.440
Well...

01:20:57.774 --> 01:20:58.844
maybe, uh...

01:21:00.077 --> 01:21:02.247
maybe you should
just stay put.

01:22:21.959 --> 01:22:24.962
Mudroom's right across
the hall if you need anything.

01:22:26.797 --> 01:22:27.933
Okay.

01:22:30.469 --> 01:22:32.837
You can stay
as long as you want to.

01:22:35.206 --> 01:22:36.440
Thanks.

01:22:40.444 --> 01:22:42.046
I'm glad you called.

01:22:45.416 --> 01:22:47.019
Well, I'm glad you picked up.

01:23:16.081 --> 01:23:17.549
<i>Then we'll go on.</i>

01:23:19.216 --> 01:23:20.551
<i>Doesn't matter where.</i>

01:23:21.452 --> 01:23:23.322
<i>Maybe we'll run over
to Arizona.</i>

01:23:24.255 --> 01:23:25.589
<i>The roads are straight.</i>

01:23:26.523 --> 01:23:27.892
<i>And we'll build a house.</i>

01:23:29.460 --> 01:23:30.962
<i>Yeah, we'll build a house.</i>

01:23:32.529 --> 01:23:34.899
<i>Because if I'm not grounded
pretty soon...</i>

01:23:36.099 --> 01:23:37.669
<i>I'm going to go into orbit.</i>

01:24:36.059 --> 01:24:37.428
Jewel, wake up.

01:24:39.697 --> 01:24:41.797
I need to go out for a bit.
Do you need anything?

01:24:41.799 --> 01:24:46.438
No. How long
you gonna be gone?

01:24:47.304 --> 01:24:48.640
Not long.

01:25:16.000 --> 01:25:17.068
Hello?

01:25:18.803 --> 01:25:19.735
Hello?

01:25:19.737 --> 01:25:20.939
<i>Hey, John.</i>

01:25:22.172 --> 01:25:23.675
Yeah, it is.

01:25:26.376 --> 01:25:28.513
- Who's this?
<i>- How's it going?</i>

01:25:30.514 --> 01:25:31.816
Forrest Tucker.

01:25:33.251 --> 01:25:34.883
Is that you?

01:25:34.885 --> 01:25:38.154
- <i>I heard you got out.</i>
- Yeah, I got out all right.

01:25:38.156 --> 01:25:41.490
What happened? Did you
get tired of digging tunnels

01:25:41.492 --> 01:25:43.194
and climbing fences?

01:25:44.394 --> 01:25:46.764
<i>Well, I thought so, but, uh...</i>

01:25:49.500 --> 01:25:50.868
<i>Forrest?</i>

01:25:52.336 --> 01:25:54.337
<i>Forrest, are you all right?</i>

01:25:54.339 --> 01:25:56.675
Yeah, I... I'm about to be.

